Skip the FSDP optimizer step on a non-finite global grad_norm.

Applies AFTER 0001/0002/0003 (line numbers are relative to the
0001-0003-patched miles tree at UPSTREAM_PIN). gpt-oss critic SFT exposed
this: the direction-only critic MSE feeds a tiny gradient into the gpt-oss
backbone, whose bf16 backward (attention q_proj + sinks) intermittently
amplifies it to a huge/NaN value as the backbone norm drifts up during
training (the "backbone norm grows ~linearly" instability documented in
nla/loss.py). clip_grad_norm_ cannot rescue an already-NaN gradient — it
multiplies every grad by clip/nan = nan — so without this guard the optimizer
writes NaN into the weights and every subsequent forward is NaN (observed:
clean through step 4-6, grad spike ~2.7e11, NaN cascade from step 7).

grad_norm here is the all-reduced GLOBAL value (.full_tensor().item()), so
every rank evaluates math.isfinite() identically and takes the same branch —
no rank divergence. On a skip, the loop-top self.optimizer.zero_grad() of the
next step clears the poisoned gradient. Healthy batches step normally; only
the rare pathological batch is dropped (observed ~4/19 early, FVE still
climbing -1.14 -> -0.17).

--- a/miles/backends/fsdp_utils/actor.py
+++ b/miles/backends/fsdp_utils/actor.py
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 import logging
+import math
 import os
 import random
 from argparse import Namespace
@@ -471,8 +489,19 @@ class FSDPTrainRayActor(TrainRayActor):
                 grad_norm = torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(self.model.parameters(), self.args.clip_grad)
                 grad_norm = grad_norm.full_tensor().item()

-                self.optimizer.step()
-                self.lr_scheduler.step()
+                # [NLA patch 0004] skip the optimizer step on a non-finite global
+                # grad_norm instead of writing NaN/inf into the weights (which
+                # poisons every later forward). grad_norm is the all-reduced
+                # global value, so all ranks take the same branch. The next
+                # step zeroes grads at the loop top, clearing the poisoned grad.
+                if math.isfinite(grad_norm):
+                    self.optimizer.step()
+                    self.lr_scheduler.step()
+                else:
+                    logging.getLogger(__name__).warning(
+                        f"[NLA patch 0004] skip optimizer step rollout={rollout_id} "
+                        f"step={step_id}: non-finite grad_norm={grad_norm}"
+                    )

                 if self.args.ci_test:
